COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 9:41AM PT today, over 1.6 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 27.3 thousand have died.

In the last day, 1.7 thousand new infections were reported and 9 deaths. This is trending upwards.

Fortunately, 54.8 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 85.7% have their 1st shot and 78.9% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 9 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~107 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around Nov-20 when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
